document_data.Rumors & Legends:
[[File:Mule-2e.png|thumb|273px|''A dwarf goes mining with a [[clover|four-leaf clover]] and horseshoe mounted on his hat for good luck.'']]
* One legend claimed that [[halfling]]s were the ones who invented horseshoes. This legend was likely false, as halflings typically used [[goat]]s rather than horses.
* Horseshoes were often associated with good luck and many superstitions surrounded this. It was thought by some to be very lucky to find a horseshoe in the road, especially if it had been cast off from the hind legs of a grey mare. Some thought them to be protective amulets, with farmers hanging them in barns or stables and sailors nailing them to the masts of ships.{{Cite dragon/276/Black Cats and Broken Mirrors|37}}
